---
description: Project memory & guardrails for the L1 Help Desk Copilot
alwaysApply: true
---
- **Read `CLAUDE.md` and `ROADMAP.md` first** — they are this project's source of truth (architecture, conventions, current status, backlog). Follow them; update `ROADMAP.md` as you ship.
- **Hard guardrails (never break):**
  - Never commit secrets. `.env`, `audit_log.jsonl`, `tickets.db*`, `.venv/`, `eval/last_results.json` are gitignored — verify before any push.
  - Safe defaults: mock LLM + Microsoft Graph dry-run. Lab Entra tenant + sample data only — never claim production / real users. Passwords never enter the audit log.
  - Keep changes scoped (portfolio MVP); flag scope creep. Push only when the user asks.
- Stack: Python / FastAPI + Claude + SQLite ticket store + Microsoft Graph. Run: `uvicorn app.main:app --reload` (UI http://127.0.0.1:8000/). Eval: `python -m eval.run_eval --engine both`.
